WEBVTT

00:00.359 --> 00:02.284
was your age.

00:02.286 --> 00:04.361
Walk a different part
of the property every day.

00:04.363 --> 00:06.789
He said it gave him a feel
for what kind of day
it was gonna be.

00:06.791 --> 00:08.791
Was the "first thing"
so early back then?

00:08.793 --> 00:11.627
It was even earlier,
you little rat.

00:11.629 --> 00:14.113
Remember the song
he used to sing me?
Mm.

00:14.115 --> 00:16.615
Together:
♪<i> You are my sunshine</i> ♪

00:16.617 --> 00:19.042
♪<i> My only sunshine</i> ♪

00:19.044 --> 00:21.229
Hershel:
♪<i> You make me happy</i> ♪

00:21.231 --> 00:23.547
♪<i> When skies are gray</i> ♪

00:23.549 --> 00:25.975
♪<i> You'll never know, dear</i> ♪
Morning, Barbara.

00:25.977 --> 00:28.477
♪<i> How much I love you</i> ♪
Morning, Maggie.

00:28.479 --> 00:32.481
♪<i> Please don't take</i>
<i> my sunshine away</i> ♪

00:32.483 --> 00:35.910
♪♪

00:35.912 --> 00:38.079
[Hammer pounding]

00:38.081 --> 00:44.977
♪♪

00:44.979 --> 00:47.088
Negan: Hey, I just
wanted to thank you

00:47.090 --> 00:49.832
for getting me
the hell out of Dodge.

00:49.834 --> 00:51.984
I mean, uh,
you may have noticed

00:51.986 --> 00:54.095
things with Maggie and I
are a little bit tense.

00:54.097 --> 00:56.430
I don't mind being lay-low Negan
for a bit,

00:56.432 --> 01:00.434
but, hell, there's only so far
I can go to get out of her way.

01:00.436 --> 01:03.086
♪♪

01:03.088 --> 01:05.347
You know, I was thinking,
maybe, uh --

01:05.349 --> 01:08.167
maybe you'd put in
a word for me?

01:08.169 --> 01:12.429
Smooth things over, at least
kind of get the ball rollin'.

01:12.431 --> 01:15.190
Given our
recent history,

01:15.192 --> 01:18.344
uh, I kind of figured
you owe me that much, right?

01:18.346 --> 01:21.697
♪♪

01:21.699 --> 01:24.183
You know this place?

01:24.185 --> 01:26.201
Mm-hmm.

01:26.203 --> 01:29.780
♪♪

01:29.782 --> 01:32.282
[Door opens]

01:32.284 --> 01:35.210
[Door creaks]

01:35.212 --> 01:37.096
[Birds calling]

01:41.886 --> 01:45.187
[Door creaks and closes]

01:49.210 --> 01:51.635
I see you went ahead
and moved me in.

01:51.637 --> 01:54.880
Daryl helped.
I'm sorry.

01:54.882 --> 01:56.899
The Council's voted
to banish you.

01:58.177 --> 02:00.553
What you want just
isn't gonna happen.

02:00.555 --> 02:01.737
It's not possible.

02:01.739 --> 02:04.815
I know it's not
what I promised,

02:04.817 --> 02:07.668
but given
our less-recent history,

02:07.670 --> 02:09.670
it's better
than you deserve.

02:09.672 --> 02:12.340
It is what it is,
I guess.

02:13.401 --> 02:16.418
And if you don't
mind me asking...

02:16.420 --> 02:18.737
did the Council
really banish me?

02:18.739 --> 02:21.164
Or is this more of
a "Carol seizing the reins"

02:21.166 --> 02:22.892
kind of situation?

02:26.505 --> 02:28.263
[Chuckles softly]

02:28.265 --> 02:31.317
This rabbit's for you.

02:33.512 --> 02:35.938
[ Door opens and closes ]

02:35.940 --> 02:44.346
♪♪

02:44.348 --> 02:52.696
♪♪

02:52.698 --> 03:01.037
♪♪

03:01.039 --> 03:09.379
♪♪

03:09.381 --> 03:17.655
♪♪

03:23.269 --> 03:25.228
[Fire crackling]

03:25.230 --> 03:33.328
♪♪

03:33.330 --> 03:41.529
♪♪

03:41.531 --> 03:49.662
♪♪

03:49.664 --> 03:52.088
Savior Negan:
<i> Little pig, little pig.</i>

03:52.090 --> 03:54.090
[Bat thudding]

03:54.092 --> 03:57.336
Let me in.

03:57.338 --> 04:01.173
♪♪

04:01.175 --> 04:03.767
[Chuckles]
It's all right.

04:03.769 --> 04:06.695
I know you can hear me
loud and clear.

04:06.697 --> 04:10.273
I know that nobody likes
an "I told you so."

04:10.275 --> 04:12.108
What can I say?

04:12.110 --> 04:15.521
I must be a bit of a masochist,
'cause, uh...

04:15.523 --> 04:18.299
[Laughs]

04:18.301 --> 04:20.359
You know what the sad part is?

04:20.361 --> 04:22.803
The sad part isn't
where we ended up here,

04:22.805 --> 04:24.880
'cause, I mean --
[Scoffs] Let's face it.

04:24.882 --> 04:28.124
It could have been
a hell of a lot worse.

04:28.126 --> 04:32.295
No, see, the sad part is that
you thought for even a second

04:32.297 --> 04:34.540
that those folks
would see you for anything

04:34.542 --> 04:37.133
but who you truly are...

04:37.135 --> 04:39.228
♪♪

04:39.230 --> 04:40.863
...which is me.

04:42.399 --> 04:45.050
You're a clown.

04:45.052 --> 04:47.811
A cult of personality
with no cult.

04:47.813 --> 04:50.331
You go ahead and you call me
whatever little names

04:50.333 --> 04:54.226
you want to call me,
but you gotta admit --

04:54.228 --> 04:56.003
we got a hell of a lot
further

04:56.005 --> 04:59.173
with a kind word
and good ol' Lucille here

04:59.175 --> 05:02.676
than we ever got
with just a kind word.

05:02.678 --> 05:05.679
It's time to face the facts,
old man.

05:06.999 --> 05:11.744
You are<i> nothin'</i>
without her.

05:11.746 --> 05:13.595
[Glass shatters]

05:13.597 --> 05:21.436
♪♪

05:21.438 --> 05:29.278
♪♪

05:29.280 --> 05:33.282
[Chains creaking]

05:33.284 --> 05:38.862
♪♪

05:38.864 --> 05:41.382
Rick:<i> Carl said</i>
<i> it doesn't have to be --</i>

05:41.384 --> 05:43.442
<i> it doesn't have to be</i>
<i> a fight anymore.</i>

05:43.444 --> 05:45.127
<i> He was wrong.</i>

05:45.129 --> 05:47.054
[Grunts]

05:47.056 --> 05:49.205
[Gurgling]

05:49.207 --> 05:52.117
[Thud]

05:52.119 --> 05:54.895
Negan:
<i> Look what you did.</i>

05:54.897 --> 05:58.140
<i> I want to see her.</i>
<i> I need to see her.</i>

05:58.142 --> 06:01.310
No. Negan...

06:01.312 --> 06:03.312
we don't have your bat.

06:03.314 --> 06:05.631
Where is she?
What did you do with her?

06:05.633 --> 06:07.074
She's still out there.

06:07.076 --> 06:10.060
♪♪

06:10.062 --> 06:12.580
[Crow caws]

06:12.582 --> 06:20.662
♪♪

06:20.664 --> 06:28.670
♪♪

06:28.672 --> 06:36.753
♪♪

06:36.755 --> 06:38.922
[Walker snarling]

06:38.924 --> 06:43.018
♪♪

06:43.020 --> 06:45.446
[Panting]

06:45.448 --> 06:52.386
♪♪

06:52.388 --> 06:59.201
♪♪

06:59.203 --> 07:06.041
♪♪

07:06.043 --> 07:10.212
[Snarling continues]

07:10.214 --> 07:12.714
♪♪

07:12.716 --> 07:14.216
[Snarling continues]

07:14.218 --> 07:16.143
[Thudding]

07:16.145 --> 07:18.537
♪♪

07:18.539 --> 07:21.390
[Scraping]

07:21.392 --> 07:30.716
♪♪

07:30.718 --> 07:39.983
♪♪

07:39.985 --> 07:49.176
♪♪

07:49.178 --> 07:58.577
♪♪

07:58.579 --> 08:07.769
♪♪

08:07.771 --> 08:11.256
[Panting]
Y-You gotta let me go.

08:11.258 --> 08:14.368
♪♪

08:14.370 --> 08:18.038
My wife -- she has cancer.
She needs it.

08:18.040 --> 08:21.375
Gotta keep it safe, okay?
I told you.

08:21.377 --> 08:23.101
I know.
No, it --

08:23.103 --> 08:25.103
Shh.
You keeping me here...

08:25.105 --> 08:28.048
[Shushing] I know.
...it kills me<i> and</i> her.

08:28.050 --> 08:29.566
Please, I told you.

08:29.568 --> 08:33.612
Shh. Hey. I know you did.
I know.

08:33.614 --> 08:37.391
Hey, and I told you --
my heart, it goes out to you.

08:38.585 --> 08:42.471
Can't imagine what you must
be going through right now.

08:42.473 --> 08:44.714
God. [Scoffs]

08:44.716 --> 08:48.384
Just wondering...

08:48.386 --> 08:52.147
if she's ever gonna get
her next treatment.

08:52.149 --> 08:54.742
[Chuckles]

08:56.078 --> 08:58.804
We drove out
to where you told us

08:58.806 --> 09:00.973
those doctors
gave you this stuff,

09:00.975 --> 09:03.992
but, um, they weren't there.
That's not my fault.

09:03.994 --> 09:06.236
I told you. I told you.
They move around.

09:06.238 --> 09:08.404
They were<i> never</i> there.

09:08.406 --> 09:11.925
I mean, that road,
it was so overgrown,

09:11.927 --> 09:14.244
we couldn't even get
the pickup down it.

09:14.246 --> 09:17.489
So, now...

09:17.491 --> 09:20.826
I know you can't get this stuff
just anywhere.

09:20.828 --> 09:22.828
It needs to be
refrigerated.

09:22.830 --> 09:28.350
Somebody, they took care
of this for a<i> long</i> time,

09:28.352 --> 09:31.353
and if they've got something
as rare as this...

09:31.355 --> 09:32.929
[Chuckles]

09:32.931 --> 09:35.616
...they probably got a lot
of other stuff, too.

09:35.618 --> 09:37.843
So, now...

09:37.845 --> 09:41.271
you tell me
where you got it,

09:41.273 --> 09:44.583
I am going to let you
take this to your wife.

09:46.128 --> 09:49.946
Otherwise, I'm gonna
pour it down the toilet

09:49.948 --> 09:52.024
and make you watch.

09:52.026 --> 09:54.760
Hm?

09:57.047 --> 10:00.198
[Groans]

10:00.200 --> 10:01.308
[Spits]

10:01.310 --> 10:03.218
[Panting]

10:03.220 --> 10:05.204
All right.

10:05.206 --> 10:07.556
Just please put that back
in the cooler.

10:07.558 --> 10:10.049
I will tell you
whatever you want to know.

10:10.051 --> 10:12.544
Just, please,
keep that safe.

10:12.546 --> 10:14.546
[Sighs]

10:14.548 --> 10:19.901
The part about the medical
clinic, that's all true.

10:19.903 --> 10:21.386
And, yeah, you're right --

10:21.388 --> 10:22.904
they have a medical
stockpile somewhere.

10:22.906 --> 10:25.407
They keep equipment, drugs.

10:25.409 --> 10:29.744
I don't know where, but that
is where that came from.

10:29.746 --> 10:33.656
I've been tracking 'em
for weeks.

10:33.658 --> 10:37.845
I found 'em -- I don't know --
two or three days ago.

10:37.847 --> 10:42.240
♪♪

10:42.242 --> 10:44.351
[Engine rumbling]

10:44.353 --> 10:49.672
♪♪

10:49.674 --> 10:54.862
♪♪

10:54.864 --> 10:57.531
[Groans]

10:57.533 --> 11:00.550
Drop your guns!
Drop your guns!

11:00.552 --> 11:02.444
I don't want to shoot him,
but I will!

11:02.446 --> 11:05.873
Okay. Take it easy.

11:07.042 --> 11:09.101
[Groans]

11:09.103 --> 11:12.028
[Panting]

11:12.030 --> 11:13.922
No, don't!

11:13.924 --> 11:16.108
[Body thuds]

11:16.110 --> 11:18.610
Shit. You didn't
have to do that.

11:18.612 --> 11:20.888
Better safe than sorry.

11:26.135 --> 11:28.920
[Breathing heavily]

11:28.922 --> 11:34.459
♪♪

11:34.461 --> 11:37.871
[Rattling]

11:37.873 --> 11:40.782
Take it easy, Capone.

11:42.644 --> 11:44.970
My name is Negan.

11:44.972 --> 11:46.312
[Microwave beeping]

11:46.314 --> 11:49.917
Negan. All right.

11:49.919 --> 11:51.084
I'm Franklin.

11:51.086 --> 11:53.236
[Microwave humming]

11:53.238 --> 11:54.663
[Jingling]

11:54.665 --> 11:56.906
We gonna have
any problems?

11:56.908 --> 12:00.652
No, sir.
No problems.

12:00.654 --> 12:03.488
Mm-hmm.

12:03.490 --> 12:05.432
All right.

12:08.753 --> 12:11.563
[Microwave beeps]

12:17.688 --> 12:19.595
Exposure...

12:19.597 --> 12:21.339
exhaustion...

12:21.341 --> 12:23.116
dehydration.

12:25.345 --> 12:27.996
And I think I can add
malnutrition to the list.

12:29.850 --> 12:33.276
Uh, I gotta wonder,
with a guy like you...

12:33.278 --> 12:35.095
the state you're in...

12:35.097 --> 12:39.800
trying to rob a bunch of doctors
with an empty gun.

12:42.212 --> 12:44.104
My wife has cancer.

12:44.106 --> 12:46.214
She was in the middle
of treatments

12:46.216 --> 12:47.808
when the world
went to shit,

12:47.810 --> 12:50.385
and I have just been
trying to keep her going.

12:50.387 --> 12:52.929
-So you're a doctor?
-I'm a high-school gym teacher.

12:52.931 --> 12:56.057
High school. Mm.

12:56.059 --> 12:59.469
So, what'd you mean
by "keep her going"?

12:59.471 --> 13:03.306
The doctors had given us
a calendar of what she needed

13:03.308 --> 13:05.233
and when she needed it,
so all I had to do

13:05.235 --> 13:07.995
was find the drugs and figure
out how to do infusions.

13:07.997 --> 13:10.646
Wait a minute.
So...you taught yourself

13:10.648 --> 13:12.165
how to give someone
chemotherapy?

13:12.167 --> 13:16.169
The pumps aren't
that complicated.

13:16.171 --> 13:17.879
Unless something
goes wrong.

13:17.881 --> 13:20.132
Well, did something
go wrong?

13:22.252 --> 13:25.220
Yeah.
You could say that.

13:27.999 --> 13:30.017
[Walker snarling]

13:32.763 --> 13:34.579
[Dishes clatter]

13:34.581 --> 13:37.149
[Refrigerator door creaks]

13:40.087 --> 13:42.345
[Sighs]

13:42.347 --> 13:44.156
[Refrigerator door closes]

13:48.945 --> 13:51.096
Trying to figure out what James
Bond movie I want to watch.

13:51.098 --> 13:54.023
Well, baby, I think
we're gonna have to skip
the movie just for now.

13:54.025 --> 13:56.101
Generator's making
too much noise.

13:56.103 --> 13:59.195
Hey. We're gonna
have to kill it.

13:59.197 --> 14:01.122
Why bother, right?

14:01.124 --> 14:02.865
I turn the generator off
for a little bit,

14:02.867 --> 14:04.200
and they lose interest.

14:04.202 --> 14:06.202
They always do.

14:06.204 --> 14:09.431
[Walker snarling]

14:20.051 --> 14:22.627
[Freezer humming]

14:22.629 --> 14:26.389
[Door creaks and closes]

14:26.391 --> 14:27.966
[Walker snarling]

14:27.968 --> 14:30.485
[Generator rumbling]

14:30.487 --> 14:33.396
[Generator slows and stops]

14:33.398 --> 14:36.825
[Walker snarling]

14:36.827 --> 14:40.495
[Fence rattling]

14:40.497 --> 14:43.406
"'I see what you are feeling,'
replied Charlotte.

14:43.408 --> 14:46.093
'You must be surprised,
very much surprised --

14:46.095 --> 14:49.763
so lately as Mr. Collins
was wishing to marry you.

14:49.765 --> 14:51.247
But when you have...'"

14:51.249 --> 14:53.749
[Sighs] Mama.

14:53.751 --> 14:55.160
Hmm?

14:55.162 --> 14:56.603
This book sucks.
It's killing me.

14:56.605 --> 14:59.255
I-I-I can't --
I can't do it.

14:59.257 --> 15:01.942
You're the one that won't
let me watch James Bond.

15:01.944 --> 15:04.277
Read.

15:04.279 --> 15:07.405
[Walker snarling,
fence rattling]

15:11.345 --> 15:14.162
You gotta take care of it.

15:16.274 --> 15:18.516
[Walker snarling]

15:18.518 --> 15:26.040
♪♪

15:26.042 --> 15:33.698
♪♪

15:33.700 --> 15:41.297
♪♪

15:41.299 --> 15:48.897
♪♪

15:48.899 --> 15:51.457
Come on. Seriously?

15:51.459 --> 15:52.842
[Gunshot]

15:52.844 --> 15:54.402
[Thud]

15:54.404 --> 15:56.888
[Crows cawing]

15:56.890 --> 15:59.799
♪♪

15:59.801 --> 16:02.560
That was our last bullet.

16:02.562 --> 16:05.488
Hey.

16:05.490 --> 16:07.507
Are you all right?
Uh-huh.

16:09.260 --> 16:11.903
Turn the generator back on.
I want to watch a movie.

16:11.905 --> 16:18.310
♪♪

16:30.281 --> 16:33.516
♪♪

16:33.518 --> 16:36.277
[Birds chirping]

16:36.279 --> 16:45.145
♪♪

16:45.147 --> 16:48.273
[Spits]

16:48.275 --> 16:57.131
♪♪

16:57.133 --> 17:06.048
♪♪

17:06.050 --> 17:14.908
♪♪

17:14.910 --> 17:16.076
How you doing?

17:16.078 --> 17:18.636
I'm good.

17:18.638 --> 17:20.989
I got something for you.

17:20.991 --> 17:25.026
I found someone's stash.
[Chuckles]

17:25.028 --> 17:27.328
Now, it's a little bit
dried out,

17:27.330 --> 17:31.574
but this is gonna help
with your nausea.

17:31.576 --> 17:34.669
You're having to go further
and further every time.

17:34.671 --> 17:36.746
Well, generator
needs gas,

17:36.748 --> 17:38.840
and this place
has been picked over.

17:38.842 --> 17:41.917
But the bright side is...
that I reckon

17:41.919 --> 17:43.753
that's exactly
what's keeping us safe.

17:43.755 --> 17:45.905
There is nothing here
that anybody wants.

17:45.907 --> 17:48.090
You can't keep it up.

17:48.092 --> 17:51.111
We need to move.
We need other people.

17:53.215 --> 17:55.507
It's just too dangerous
out there.

17:55.509 --> 17:57.859
That's my point.

17:57.861 --> 18:00.361
Baby, you have
three treatments left.

18:00.363 --> 18:01.937
That's it, okay?

18:01.939 --> 18:03.848
So we are gonna get
your strength up,

18:03.850 --> 18:05.775
and then I will put you
on my motorcycle

18:05.777 --> 18:07.610
and I will take you
wherever you want to go --

18:07.612 --> 18:10.130
wherever
you can dream up.

18:10.132 --> 18:11.756
I promise.

18:13.168 --> 18:15.193
Okay.
Okay.

18:15.195 --> 18:17.137
[Generator thumping]

18:19.366 --> 18:21.266
[Shivering]

18:24.479 --> 18:27.797
♪<i> You are</i> ♪

18:27.799 --> 18:30.224
♪<i> So beautiful</i> ♪

18:30.226 --> 18:31.709
♪<i> To me</i> ♪

18:31.711 --> 18:33.653
[Chuckles]

18:33.655 --> 18:35.971
♪<i> Can't you see</i> ♪

18:35.973 --> 18:40.309
♪<i> You're everything</i>
<i> I hope for</i> ♪

18:40.311 --> 18:43.163
♪<i> You're everything</i>
<i> I need</i> ♪

18:43.165 --> 18:47.467
♪<i> 'Cause you are</i> ♪

18:47.469 --> 18:49.485
♪<i> So beautiful</i> ♪

18:49.487 --> 18:52.063
♪♪

18:52.065 --> 18:54.156
♪<i> To me</i> ♪

18:54.158 --> 19:01.156
♪♪

19:01.158 --> 19:08.079
♪♪

19:08.081 --> 19:09.839
[Walker snarling]

19:09.841 --> 19:12.767
Ugh. Damn it.

19:12.769 --> 19:15.195
Lucille: It's not like
killing a person, babe.

19:15.197 --> 19:17.755
It's not even like
killing an animal.

19:17.757 --> 19:20.166
You can't let it
keep bothering you.

19:20.168 --> 19:22.869
It doesn't bother me.
I...

19:22.871 --> 19:25.780
I'm just worried that
I'm gonna get used to it.

19:25.782 --> 19:27.374
[Snarling continues]

19:29.378 --> 19:31.452
Okay.

19:31.454 --> 19:34.005
Go turn
the generator off.

19:37.201 --> 19:39.719
How, um...

19:39.721 --> 19:41.279
How's your dinner?

19:41.281 --> 19:42.705
It was really good.

19:42.707 --> 19:44.724
If I had known

19:44.726 --> 19:48.395
that dog food
could taste like this...

19:48.397 --> 19:51.714
I would have been eating
that shit all along.

19:51.716 --> 19:54.626
[Both laughing]

19:54.628 --> 19:56.294
Oh, God.

19:56.296 --> 19:58.571
[Laughs]

19:58.573 --> 20:00.055
Hey.

20:00.057 --> 20:01.482
Hmm?

20:01.484 --> 20:03.058
Happy anniversary.

20:03.060 --> 20:04.560
Happy anniver--

20:04.562 --> 20:06.395
