♪<i> To me</i> ♪

38:45.924 --> 38:48.108
[Fire crackling]

38:48.110 --> 38:50.536
[Motorcycle departs]

39:01.739 --> 39:03.841
[Thud]

39:05.219 --> 39:08.086
[Grunts]

39:08.088 --> 39:11.873
Craven: All right.
Okay. That's enough.

39:11.875 --> 39:14.542
[Chuckles]

39:14.544 --> 39:17.637
You know,
it's been a long day.

39:17.639 --> 39:20.123
I -- I did not get
much sleep last night,

39:20.125 --> 39:24.461
so this is gonna be
the last time I ask.

39:24.463 --> 39:27.881
Tell me where you keep
the good stuff,

39:27.883 --> 39:29.891
or I'm gonna bring out the girl.

39:29.893 --> 39:32.319
Hmm? [Chuckles]

39:32.321 --> 39:35.706
She's a little young for you,
don't you think?

39:39.569 --> 39:41.837
[Generator rumbling]

39:48.487 --> 39:49.669
[Blow lands]

39:49.671 --> 39:52.080
[Man grunts]

39:52.082 --> 39:58.252
♪♪

39:58.254 --> 40:01.181
[ Footsteps approach ]

40:01.183 --> 40:08.422
♪♪

40:08.424 --> 40:10.765
[Gunshot]

40:10.767 --> 40:14.102
What the hell's
going on out there?

40:14.104 --> 40:16.346
Man on radio:<i> Stay there.</i>
<i> We're checking it out.</i>

40:16.348 --> 40:19.440
Eh. Go take a look.
Man: Over here!

40:19.442 --> 40:21.943
He's over here!

40:21.945 --> 40:23.295
[Gunfire]

40:23.297 --> 40:24.688
[Glass shatters]

40:24.690 --> 40:26.247
[Wood snaps]

40:26.249 --> 40:28.433
[Gunshots]
Can one of you idiots

40:28.435 --> 40:30.469
tell me what the hell
is going on out there?!

40:30.471 --> 40:32.787
[Gunfire, man screams]

40:32.789 --> 40:34.806
Man: I'm dropping my gun!
Please!

40:34.808 --> 40:36.808
[Gunshot, man grunts,
body thuds]

40:36.810 --> 40:41.705
♪♪

40:41.707 --> 40:45.558
[Footsteps approach slowly]

40:45.560 --> 40:47.560
[Rhythmic knocking on door]

40:47.562 --> 40:50.380
♪♪

40:50.382 --> 40:51.731
[Glass shatters]

40:51.733 --> 40:54.600
[Gunshots]

40:54.602 --> 41:01.800
♪♪

41:01.802 --> 41:03.802
[Groaning]

41:03.804 --> 41:05.578
[Gun cocks]

41:05.580 --> 41:09.582
♪♪

41:09.584 --> 41:11.468
[Groans]

41:15.015 --> 41:17.090
Are there
any more of them?

41:17.092 --> 41:18.817
I think I got all of 'em.

41:18.819 --> 41:20.310
[Groaning]

41:20.312 --> 41:22.078
You take this.

41:22.080 --> 41:24.915
You go find your daughter,
make sure she's okay.

41:24.917 --> 41:26.942
[Craven groaning]

41:29.530 --> 41:31.438
Okay.

41:31.440 --> 41:37.260
♪♪

41:37.262 --> 41:39.187
[Craven groans]

41:39.189 --> 41:44.025
♪♪

41:44.027 --> 41:45.510
[Sighs]

41:45.512 --> 41:48.939
Well. Look at us.

41:48.941 --> 41:51.942
Here we are again.

41:51.944 --> 41:56.722
You know, last time we did this,
you said that I talk too much.

41:56.724 --> 41:58.557
Bad news is,
I got some stuff

41:58.559 --> 42:01.117
to get off my chest
this time, as well.

42:01.119 --> 42:04.545
[Groans]
But, see, this time...

42:04.547 --> 42:07.958
This time, you'd best hope
I<i> never</i> stop talking...

42:07.960 --> 42:10.718
because when I do --

42:10.720 --> 42:14.555
when I do, something very
terrible is gonna happen to you.

42:14.557 --> 42:18.468
You know I never killed a man
before tonight?

42:18.470 --> 42:21.705
It's the truth.
Came close once.

42:23.566 --> 42:28.311
See, there was this -- this bar
my wife and I used to go to.

42:28.313 --> 42:30.480
It was our favorite bar.
It was our favorite bar 'cause

42:30.482 --> 42:32.315
it had our favorite jukebox.

42:32.317 --> 42:37.153
Favorite jukebox because, well,
it had our favorite song.

42:37.155 --> 42:42.158
"You Are So Beautiful"
by the one and only Joe Cocker.

42:42.160 --> 42:44.344
Probably the greatest
love ballad ever written.

42:44.346 --> 42:46.496
I'm sure you agree.

42:46.498 --> 42:48.832
But, see, there was...

42:48.834 --> 42:52.352
there was this guy.

42:52.354 --> 42:54.762
This guy, he had, uh --

42:54.764 --> 42:58.358
he had one of those voices
you can't unhear.

42:58.360 --> 43:01.361
Yeah, it was like, um,
my brain had been hijacked,

43:01.363 --> 43:03.789
and I can't --
I can't think anymore.

43:03.791 --> 43:06.516
Anyway, he is talking
and laughing

43:06.518 --> 43:09.610
while the song is playing,
being completely obnoxious.

43:09.612 --> 43:12.113
So my beautiful wife, Lucille,

43:12.115 --> 43:15.967
she gets up,
goes over to where he is,

43:15.969 --> 43:18.778
and politely asks him
if he could keep it down

43:18.780 --> 43:20.864
so she could hear her song.

43:20.866 --> 43:25.477
Well, let's just say
he chose poorly.

43:25.479 --> 43:27.704
So now<i> I</i> gotta get up.

43:27.706 --> 43:32.542
And I go over, and I tell him
that he owes me 50 cents

43:32.544 --> 43:36.304
so I can play the song again
and he can shut the hell up

43:36.306 --> 43:39.399
and my wife can enjoy her song.

43:39.401 --> 43:40.900
♪♪

43:40.902 --> 43:42.886
Now, here's the important part,

43:42.888 --> 43:46.222
and I<i> really</i> want you
to pay attention to this.

43:46.224 --> 43:50.076
You know when people get
so angry they say they see red?

43:50.078 --> 43:53.229
That shit is actually true.

43:53.231 --> 43:56.341
When this asshole comes at me,
all I see is red.

43:56.343 --> 43:59.586
It's like I am looking
at the world through blood.

43:59.588 --> 44:02.422
So I wail on him.

44:02.424 --> 44:06.351
I wail on this son of a bitch
until he's not moving.

44:06.353 --> 44:08.595
And then I reach down,
I grab his wallet,

44:08.597 --> 44:11.172
and I take out one dollar,

44:11.174 --> 44:14.918
and I play her song again.

44:14.920 --> 44:16.862
Twice.

44:16.864 --> 44:19.606
Turns out that this prick

44:19.608 --> 44:24.594
has kids that go to the school
that I teach gym at.

44:24.596 --> 44:27.764
Needless to say,
the school was...

44:27.766 --> 44:29.708
unthrilled.

44:29.710 --> 44:31.877
I get fired. This guy sues me.

44:31.879 --> 44:34.129
I don't have a job,
so now my wife

44:34.131 --> 44:36.789
has to pay his medical bills.

44:36.791 --> 44:39.533
So, t-the point of this is,

44:39.535 --> 44:42.220
there were consequences
to me seeing red.

44:42.222 --> 44:44.614
Seeing red was a bad thing then.

44:44.616 --> 44:49.285
I was a bad man...then.

44:49.287 --> 44:52.972
But, see, now,
nobody's suing anybody.

44:52.974 --> 44:55.883
Nobody's gettin' fired.
Hell, nobody's keeping score.

44:55.885 --> 44:58.645
Now when I see red,

44:58.647 --> 45:03.133
it's just a question
of what I am capable of.

45:03.135 --> 45:06.970
And, well, man,
I hate to break it to ya.

45:06.972 --> 45:08.638
See, I am startin' to think

45:08.640 --> 45:12.566
that I am capable
of damn near anything.

45:12.568 --> 45:17.055
♪♪

45:17.057 --> 45:20.425
So this...

45:20.427 --> 45:23.720
this is for<i> not</i> killing me.

45:25.507 --> 45:27.415
[Blow lands, Craven grunts]

45:27.417 --> 45:29.893
[Walker snarling]

45:47.287 --> 45:54.851
♪♪

45:54.853 --> 46:02.283
♪♪

46:02.285 --> 46:05.028
I am sorry that I left you.

46:05.030 --> 46:06.287
♪♪

46:06.289 --> 46:07.955
I was a coward.

46:07.957 --> 46:12.143
I couldn't face the pain
of losing you, so I ran away.

46:12.145 --> 46:14.295
And then I made myself
not feel anything

46:14.297 --> 46:16.630
because I didn't want
to feel the shame.

46:16.632 --> 46:18.817
The problem is that...

46:18.819 --> 46:21.561
shame is the one thing
that I still feel.

46:21.563 --> 46:24.472
♪♪

46:24.474 --> 46:28.885
Uh, I'm sorry
that you went out like that.

46:28.887 --> 46:30.737
I should have been there.

46:30.739 --> 46:35.391
I am sorry that I named a stupid
baseball bat after you.

46:35.393 --> 46:38.228
♪♪

46:38.230 --> 46:41.414
I am sorry for all the pain
that I put you through.

46:41.416 --> 46:47.161
♪♪

46:47.163 --> 46:49.330
I hope that you found someone
in the afterlife

46:49.332 --> 46:52.592
and you are screwing
your brains out.

46:52.594 --> 46:55.745
Well...

46:55.747 --> 46:57.914
not really, but...

46:57.916 --> 46:59.749
fair is fair.

46:59.751 --> 47:03.586
♪♪

47:03.588 --> 47:05.513
I miss you.

47:05.515 --> 47:08.182
♪♪

47:08.184 --> 47:10.610
I love the shit out of you.

47:10.612 --> 47:13.763
♪♪

47:13.765 --> 47:16.616
And I am gonna do
your fighting for you.

47:16.618 --> 47:26.051
♪♪

47:26.053 --> 47:35.618
♪♪

47:35.620 --> 47:45.052
♪♪

47:45.054 --> 47:54.487
♪♪

47:54.489 --> 47:56.581
[ Indistinct conversations ]

47:56.583 --> 47:58.566
[Leaves rustling]

47:58.568 --> 48:05.090
♪♪

48:05.092 --> 48:11.821
♪♪

48:11.823 --> 48:18.344
♪♪

48:18.346 --> 48:20.438
Where's the A-Team
off to?

48:20.440 --> 48:23.349
Looking for food in
an Army base Daryl found.

48:23.351 --> 48:26.502
We find anything,
I'll bring some by your cabin.

48:26.504 --> 48:28.546
Nah, that won't be
necessary.

48:28.548 --> 48:32.525
In fact, that whole situation
isn't gonna work out.

48:32.527 --> 48:35.453
I came by here hoping
that maybe you could
requisition a cart for me.

48:35.455 --> 48:38.089
I can bring back my stuff.

48:38.091 --> 48:40.959
Yeah, I'll ask Gabriel
to approve that.

48:40.961 --> 48:43.019
♪♪

48:43.021 --> 48:45.855
If you stay here,
she<i> will</i> kill you.

48:45.857 --> 48:49.859
I just didn't want your death
on my conscience, and...

48:49.861 --> 48:51.694
now it's not.

48:51.696 --> 48:53.954
Fair enough.

48:53.956 --> 49:00.036
♪♪

